The families were on holiday at the Blinkwater self-catering lodge, just outside Upington in the Northern Cape. JOHANNESBURG - A tenth person has died in the Blinkwater Lodge fire in the Kalahari. 36-year-old Frans Davin died from severe burns at the Melomed Hospital in Bellvillle, Cape Town. Nine other people from three families died when a fire broke out early Sunday morning at the lodge. READ: Police probing deadly Cape crash Six children, two men, and a woman died in the blaze. The families were on holiday at the Blinkwater self-catering lodge, just outside Upington in the Northern Cape. Davin’s wife, Wilmien, and their one-year-old daughter are the only survivors at this stage.